^en137a (d) What should be understood as ^i[virtue consisting in purification not adhered to] is trainers’ virtue, because it is not adhered to by {false} view, and ordinary men’s virtue when not adhered to by greed. Like the virtue of the Elder Tissa the Landowner’s Son (^i[Kuṭumbiyaputta-Tissa-thera]). 
