thus: The materiality occurring in the two months of the rains (^i[vassāna]) ceases there without reaching the autumn (^i[sarada]). 
The materiality occurring in the autumn … 
in the winter (^i[hemanta) …] 
in the cool (^i[sisira]) …
in the spring (^i[vasanta]) … 
the materiality occurring in the summer (^i[gimha]) ceases there without reaching the rains again: 
therefore it is impermanent too, painful, not-self.
