^en62t^i[2. (n)] Next he divides a single footstep into six parts as “lifting up,” “shifting forward,” “shifting sideways,” “lowering down,” “placing down,” and “fixing down^f21 .”
^en63t Herein, ^i[lifting up] is raising the foot from the ground. 
^i[Shifting forward] is shifting it to the front. 
^i[Shifting sideways] is moving the foot to one side or the other in seeing a thorn, stump, snake, and so on. 
